name: Peaches

name: Bedford Hall

name: Doris
directions: There is a first floor bathroom (accessible) and then there are three bathrooms downstairs. All are gender neutral, all private single stalls with functioning locks.
comment: It's a bar, so do you, though only open 5pm-2am, but no one will bother you about using the bathroom! Also, staff is nice. Alert them if you need assistance or do not feel safe.

name: Franklin Park

Open 6pm to 4am
Just go in and use the bathroom, no purchase required!

name: Starbucks
directions: This Starbucks is near Brooklyn College and the Flatbush Junction.  There is one genderfree, single-occupancy bathroom with a locking door.  Walk in and go straight past the counter, the bathroom will be on the left.  The door is usually open for anyone to use the bathroom.
comment: As of spring 2009, regular hours are Mon-Fri 6am-10pm, and Sat-Sun 7:30am-10pm.  During college breaks, they often close early.  Call them at 718-338-2489 to check hours.

name: Brooklyn College Library Cafe
directions: There are 3 gender-neutral, single-stall bathrooms in the Library Cafe near Whitehead Hall.  One of the bathrooms is accessible.
comment: The Library Cafe is open 24 hours a day except certain holidays.  You must show a student or staff ID to enter the Brooklyn College campus.

name: Milk and Honey Cafe
directions: Ground floor, back of cafe

name: Brooklyn Public Library
directions: There's one single stall, non-gendered bathroom at the front of the library. There are going to be renovations, so that might change, but as of February 24th, 2017, this is the case.
comment: You don't have to have a library card or even be using the library.
